HEADWORD: Diarthrosis
<hw>Di`ar*thro"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to joint, articulate; <grk>dia`</grk> through, asunder
+ <?/ to fasten by a joint, <grk>'a`rqron</grk> joint.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A form of articulation which admits of
considerable motion; a complete joint; abarticulation. See
<er>Articulation</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

